On Mon, 5 May 2003, Jeff Scarbrough wrote:

> Vice-Grips have a sharp corner that will break or weaken the fuel
> line.  Valves are OK, but complicated...  The Big Tool Truck will have a
> hose pinching solution, or go to Sears.com. select tools, and search for

I used vise grips for decades without problems - be sure to squeeze them
down carefully, not allowing the fuel line to get caught in the edge of
the jaws, and you'll be fine, until you install an inline valve.

